-- Flight Cancellations Top 150 as Chicago Storm Lingers
-- B y   B i l l   K o e n i g
-- 2010-10-27T16:51:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/airlines-at-chicago-s-o-hare-cancel-more-than-150-flights-as-winds-persist.html
Chicago Department of Aviation said
airlines operating at O’Hare International Airport have canceled
more than 150 flights today and are experiencing delays
averaging 60 minutes.  Carriers operating at Midway Airport have had “minor
delays,” the department said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Koenig at 
 wkoenig@bloomberg.net  